casebody.data:
Owen Walter SMITH, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 6133. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Sept. 18, 1930. Lord & Moulton, of Portland, Or., for appellant. George Neuner, U. S. Atty., of Portland, Or.

Before DIETRICH and WILBUR, Circuit Judges, and WEBSTER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of appellee, ordered appeal dismissed for failure of appellant to print record and file brief before ease called for argument.
